energy_drains:
- Back-to-back meetings with no recovery time
- Saying yes to things I should say no to
- Other people's emergencies becoming my emergencies
- Feeling like I'm behind no matter how much I do
energy_restores:
- Early morning before anyone else is awake
- Long runs alone
- Cancelling plans (guilty pleasure)
- Completing something and crossing it off
identity_statements: I am someone who gets things done. I am someone people rely on. I am someone who pushes through when others give up. I am someone who is tired. I am someone who doesn't know how to slow down. I am someone who measures worth by output.
others_describe: They'd say I'm dependable, maybe too dependable. They'd say I seem to have it all together. Some might say I'm hard to really know. My partner would say I'm always distracted, never fully present.
automatic_behaviors:
- Check email before getting out of bed
- Say 'I'm fine' when asked how I am
- Take on more than I should in meetings
- Work during lunch
- Think about work while trying to fall asleep
- Apologize for things that aren't my fault
keystone_behaviors:
- Morning run (when I do it, everything is better)
- Weekly planning on Sunday
- Getting 7+ hours of sleep (rare but transformative)
natural_strengths:
- Executing under pressure
- Seeing the big picture while handling details
- Making others feel confident in my abilities
- Working long hours without complaining
resistance_patterns:
- Setting boundaries (I know I should but I can't)
- Delegating (it's faster if I just do it myself)
- Rest without guilt
- Asking for help
